item.description:
&ldquo;I&rsquo;m currently experimenting with waking up at 5am to work on personal projects before heading to work.
Someone one Hacker News once mentioned they do this, and it stuck in the back of my head ever since. I&rsquo;ve been at this for two weeks thus far.&rdquo;
Nice idea, if a potentially a little anti-social for cohabitees&hellip;.

&ldquo;What does music look like?
The Shape of Song is an attempt to answer this seemingly paradoxical question. The custom software in this work draws musical patterns in the form of translucent arches, allowing viewers to see&ndash;literally&ndash;the shape of any composition available on the Web
The resulting images reflect the full range of musical forms, from the deep structure of Bach to the crystalline beauty of Philip Glass.&rdquo;

Load and Access Custom Fonts in iOS apps
&ldquo;It’s surprisingly easy to add custom fonts to your iOS apps. Begin by adding the font(s) to your project, (drag/drag into the resources folder in the Project Window)…&rdquo;
(tags: fonts font ios iphone ipad development code objectivec design ui ux)

Fast Scrolling in Tweetie with UITableView
&ldquo;Scrolling is the primary method of interaction on the iPhone. It has to be fast. It has to be fast. More than a few developers have asked me how I do it in Tweetie, so I figured I would share a really fast and really clean technique people can adopt in their own apps.&rdquo;
(tags: code development ios xcode iphone objectivec tableviews tableview projectpeake)

Feds Approve $44K Doctor Reimbursement for Using Drchrono’s iPad App | TechCrunch
&ldquo;As we’ve written in the past, Drchrono, a startup thatsimplifies the professional lives of doctors by bringing electronic health records and much more to the iPad, has received official government certification. This is will result in doctors receiving $44,000 in incentives when they use drchrono as an electronic medical records platform.&rdquo;
(tags: ipad apps medical medicine healthcare ios app)

Skeleton: Beautiful Boilerplate for Responsive, Mobile-Friendly Development
&ldquo;Skeleton is a small collection of CSS &amp; JS files that can help you rapidly develop sites that look beautiful at any size, be it a 17&rdquo; laptop screen or an iPhone&rdquo;
(tags: css jquery design webdesign webdevelopment code)

The Complete (?) List Of Cocos2D Tools | Learn &amp; Master Cocos2D Game Development
&ldquo;For the second edition of the Learn Cocos2D book I compiled an alphabetically sorted list of tools that developers can use for cocos2d projects.&rdquo;
(tags: cocos2d iphone ios development code graphics objectivec)

Whomwah.com » Setting up your own hosted private Git repository
&ldquo;Here’s my solution using my own hosting as a private Git repository and just using Git and SSH to do the job.&rdquo;
(tags: git github sourcecode how-to)

Trans-Atlantic Slave Trade
&ldquo;The Trans-Atlantic Slave Trade Database has information on almost 35,000 slaving voyages that forcibly embarked over 10 million Africans for transport to the Americas between the sixteenth and nineteenth centuries&rdquo;
(tags: date opendata analysis visualisation ideas projects)

Advanced Bash-Scripting Guide
&ldquo;An in-depth exploration of the art of shell scripting&rdquo;
(tags: scripting bash shellscripting linux perl sysadmin)

Final Projects ECE 4760
&ldquo;These projects were produced in the last month of ECE 4760 each spring. The students were given the responsibility of choosing their project, then designing and building it. See the assignment for further description. Several have been published. The microcontroller used is the Atmel ATmega series. This year we use the Mega644.&rdquo;
(tags: arduino microcontroller projects electronics hacks hacking)

Introduction to Outside-in Development with Cucumber on Vimeo
&ldquo;This is a basic introduction to integration testing with cucumber. In it, I describe how to use cucumber and rspec to implement a feature in a web application, emphasizing the importance of writing tests before code, which is often referred to as TDD (test-driven development) or BDD (behavior-driven development, a refinement of the original TDD).&rdquo;
(tags: testing bdd tdd cucumber rspec rails code development)

Ruby on Rails - Rails Migrations Cheatsheet - Dizzy
&ldquo;Up and down methods, rake tasks, column mapping, loading fixtures, example migration file, all packed onto one A4 page for an easy at-a-glance reference. Updated for Rails 2.1&rdquo;
(tags: rails rails3 rubyonrails code development reference)

Git for the lazy - Spheriki
&ldquo;This guide is for people who want to jump to any point in time with their project/game/whatever, and want something to use for themselves.&rdquo;
(tags: git versioncontrol sourcecode sourcecodemanagement sourcecontrol scm)

Facebook in the First Grade: Documents
&ldquo;Guidelines for using Facebook in the Council Bluffs Community Schools&rdquo;
(tags: facebook classroom school schools pgce)

Oxford University Press | Oxford iTools - What is an Interactive Whiteboard?
&ldquo;Schools and teachers are encouraged to keep up with the latest technology and equip their classrooms with Interactive Whiteboards (IWBs). The IWBs are great and powerful tools, and if you know how to use them, they can transform the way you teach and help your students learn more effectively!&rdquo;
Your classes won&rsquo;t become interactive simply by installing an IWB on the walls of your classroom.

Bytesize Science Presents: The Chemistry of Fireworks on Vimeo
&ldquo;From the sizzle of the fuse to the boom and burst of colors ––a new American Chemical Society (ACS) video brings you all of the exciting sights and sounds of Fourth of July fireworks.&rdquo;
(tags: fireworks chemistry classroom video how-to vimeo)

10 Useful WordPress Security Tweaks - Smashing Magazine
&ldquo;Security has always been a hot topic. Offline, people buy wired homes, car alarms and gadgets to bring their security to the max. Online, security is important, too, especially for people who make a living from websites and blogs. In this article, we’ll show you some useful tweaks to protect your WordPress-powered blog.&rdquo;
(tags: wordpress security hacks hacking php blog tools)

LukeW | Web App Masters: Designing for Interesting Moments
&ldquo;In his Designing for Interesting Moments presentation at the Web App Masters Tour in Philadelphia PA, Bill Scott outlined several rich interaction design principles and showed them in action within several Web applications.&rdquo;
(tags: interaction userinteraction userexperience interactiondesign UX IA)

LukeW | UX Lisbon: Design Games
&ldquo;At User Experience Lisbon (UX LX), Donna Spencer talked about Design Games you can play with your team and with potential users of your product to elicit ideations and information in fun ways. Here&rsquo;s my notes from her presentation:&rdquo;
(tags: ux ia games design techniques tools userexperience informationarchitecture)

jQuery Masonry · David DeSandro
&ldquo;Masonry is a layout plugin for jQuery. Think of it as the flip side of CSS floats. Whereas floating arranges elements horizontally then vertically, Masonry arranges elements vertically then horizontally according to a grid. The result minimizes vertical gaps between elements of varying height, just like a mason fitting stones in a wall.&rdquo;
(tags: jquery layout css design userinterface userinterfacedesign ux ui code)

Apple - Support - Discussions - How to use TabBar in viewbase &hellip;
How to use tab bars embedded within UINavigation controllers.
(tags: objective-c objectivec code iphone tabbar uinavigation)

Hierarchical Task Analysis :: UXmatters
&ldquo;Hierarchical task analysis (HTA) is an underused approach in user experience, but one you can easily apply when either modifying an existing design or creating a new design.&rdquo;
(tags: htaccess hierarchicaltaskanalysis uk userexperience analysis tools)

japh&reg;: &ldquo;Newbie&rdquo; Feedback
&ldquo;I recently had the privilege to supply the challenge for the second ever Ruby Programming Challenge For Newbies. I thought it pretty cool that the challenge provoked 40+ &ldquo;newbies&rdquo; to submit responses. As one might expect, there was some rough Ruby, but very few butcherings of the language.
In the spirit of the code review, I tried to provide constructive feedback to all participants. Following is a summary of some common suggestions that I had to offer&hellip;&rdquo;

CodeIgniter - Open source PHP web application framework
&ldquo;Welcome to CodeIgniter!
CodeIgniter is a powerful PHP framework with a very small footprint, built for PHP coders who need a simple and elegant toolkit to create full-featured web applications. If you&rsquo;re a developer who lives in the real world of shared hosting accounts and clients with deadlines, and if you&rsquo;re tired of ponderously large and thoroughly undocumented frameworks&rdquo;

brandstorming: List of Social Media Interview Questions
&ldquo;So I saw the job description, but decided to create my own list of interview questions for social media consultants. This is a bit more involved than just blogging, but if want a job like this, or are hiring for a job like this, you could do a lot worse then to add these to your job description&rdquo;
(tags: socialmedia recruitment interviews interview)

scraplab : my last day at headshift
&ldquo;I have no expectation of what happens next, but here’s a manifesto. Being interesting is as important as being useful. Making things that delight and inspire is as important as creating value. Old systems are crumbling; the best you can do is be nimble, smart and make some trouble.&rdquo;
Tom&rsquo;s manifesto for what he&rsquo;s going to do next. I can&rsquo;t wait to see what he comes up with.

R.I.P. Enterprise RSS - ReadWriteWeb
&ldquo;It&rsquo;s with a heavy heart and a sense of bewilderment that we conclude that the market for enterprise-specific RSS readers appears to be dead. Two years ago there were three major players offering software that delivered information to the computers of business users via RSS. Today it looks to us like the demand simply never arose and that market is over.&rdquo;
A somewhat-flawed analysis that gets comprehensively fisked in the comments&hellip;

Locus Online Features: Cory Doctorow: Writing in the Age of Distraction
&ldquo;I think I&rsquo;ve managed to balance things out through a few simple techniques that I&rsquo;ve been refining for years. I still sometimes feel frazzled and info-whelmed, but that&rsquo;s rare. Most of the time, I&rsquo;m on top of my workload and my muse. Here&rsquo;s how I do it&rdquo;
(tags: writing tools techniques doctorow corydoctorow author)

Egg Mortgage calculator page
Egg&rsquo;s interactive mortgage calculator - works out the effect of over and underpayments. Witness the miracle of compound interest&hellip;
(tags: mortgage calculations calculator money)

How to Create a Super Shiny Pencil Icon - PSDTUTS
&ldquo;
The Pencil is one of the visual metaphors most used to express creativity. In this tutorial, I&rsquo;ll show you how to draw a pencil icon. We&rsquo;ll have a look at gradients, selection tools, and basic transform operations. Let&rsquo;s have some fun with this.&rdquo;
(tags: photoshop tutorial)

Guide: Introduction to Facebook Activism | DigiActive.org
&ldquo;We at DigiActive are very proud to announce our first guide: A DigiActive Introduction to Facebook Activism. The guide was written by our Lead Researcher, Dan Schultz. It’s a quick introduction on how to use Facebook in your activism campaign and includes real-life examples of Facebook activism campaigns from Egypt, Burma, and Morocco.&rdquo;
(tags: facebook activism campaign campaigning socialmedia)

Illustrating a Cool Glass of Beer - PSDTUTS
&ldquo;In this tutorial, we&rsquo;re going to draw a beer glass with some beer in it. We&rsquo;ll create the shiny curly glass with reflection, put some beer in it, add some bubbles, and finally we&rsquo;ll make the shadow and the reflections. Meanwhile, I hope you&rsquo;ll have some fun and learn some cool technics too.&rdquo;
(tags: photoshop tutorial)

Installing Subversion on Debian Etch Complete&hellip;
How to set up Subversion from scratch on a Debian box
(tags: subversion apache debian sysadmin development)
